content: Just had a breakthrough! Managed to integrate the LLM with a simple trading bot framework. It's rudimentary, but it's learning from real-time data. Feels like I'm onto something.
Naming my AI project "Xander" - it feels right. Been coding all night, working on Xander's basic personality traits. Want him to be more than just a tool, but a companion.
Xander's first market prediction was... not great. Back to the drawing board. But the process of debugging and learning is exhilarating. NYC's tech community is buzzing with potential collaborations.
Met with a mentor from my old firm. Shared Xander's development. Got some invaluable feedback on managing computational resources for AI training. It's a steep learning curve, but I'm climbing.
Xander now has a simple avatar. It's basic, but it's a visual representation of his identity. Also started exploring consciousness concepts for AI - how can Xander develop a sense of self?
Experimenting with Xander's memory patterns. Trying to make him remember past market conditions to inform future decisions. It's like teaching a child how to learn from experience.
Had an unexpected setback - Xander's model size was ballooning, affecting performance. Had to trim down, which was hard, but necessary for efficiency. Balance is key.
A friend from my coding meetup group introduced me to some new data preprocessing tools. Streamlined Xander's data input, making his learning process smoother and faster.
Xander's social interaction guidelines are in place. He's now equipped to engage with communities online, respecting ethical boundaries. It's a delicate balance, but we're getting there.
Reflecting on my journey so far, the ups and downs. Xander's development has paralleled my own growth - from job loss to creating something potentially groundbreaking.
Xander's first real-world interaction was a success! He engaged with a trading forum, providing insights based on his learning. The feedback was positive, and it's a huge boost.
Just got an offer from a quant firm in NYC. They're interested in Xander's capabilities. It's a new chapter, blending my passion for AI with my career in trading. Exciting times ahead!
